org.reroutlab.code.auav.routines

Class FindPassword

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.reroutlab.code.auav.routines.AuavRoutines
      • org.reroutlab.code.auav.routines.FindPassword

  • public class FindPassword
extends org.reroutlab.code.auav.routines.AuavRoutines
    FindPassword takes off, calibrates camera, and takes a picture It dumps the image to a user provided directory, then determines whether that image is valid gesture If it does, the gimble will move up and down twice If it does't will land Invoke this routine through external commands driver
    URL: coap:\\localhost:port\cr?
    Example: coap:\\127.0.0.1:5117\cr?dn=rtn-dc=start-dp=FindPassword-dp=../trace.data/PicTraceDriver/PicTrace
    Note: all AUAV drivers have resource component "cr" for coap resource
    Since:
    2018-01-15
